name: CSE 156L
title: Network Programming Laboratory
description: Laboratory sequence illustrating concepts taught in CSE 156. Students learn use of network programming tools and methods via programming exercises. (Formerly Computer Engineering 156L.)

pre_req_data.text: Prerequisites: CSE 150 and CSE 101. Concurrent enrollment in CSE 156 is required.

class_notes: Concurrent enrollment in CSE 156 is required. Enroll in lab and associated secondary lab.
